# << .Repo >>

`<< .Binary >>` is a single-binary Go CLI for << .Name >>, scaffolded with
`any new`. It follows the shared tamnd/*-cli conventions.

## Layout

- `cmd/<< .Binary >>/` thin main, wires `cli.Root()` into charmbracelet/fang.
- `cli/` the cobra command tree. Add subcommands here.
- `<< .LibPkg >>/` the library: HTTP client (paced, retrying, honest
  User-Agent) and the typed data models. Build endpoint calls and JSON decoding
  here, and extract reusable parts into `pkg/*` when they stand on their own.
- `docs/` a tago site deployed to GitHub Pages and `<< .Domain >>`.

## Rules

- No Go `internal/` directories. Reusable code goes in `pkg/*`.
- Pure-Go dependencies only; keep `CGO_ENABLED=0` buildable.
- Free-scraping: reverse-engineer public endpoints, no paid API key, stay polite
  with the client's pacing and retries.
- Every useful data model becomes a clean record with a JSON shape.

## Style

House voice in all text (code comments, README, docs, commits, PR bodies,
release notes): plain, direct, written by a person. No em-dashes or en-dashes,
no "X is not Y, it is Z" antithesis, no marketing vocabulary.

## Workflow

- Work on a feature branch and open a PR. Never commit to main.
- Small, focused commits with a human-voice title and body.

## Release

`git tag vX.Y.Z && git push --tags` runs GoReleaser through
`.github/workflows/release.yml`. The GHCR image tag has no `v` prefix
(`<< .Image >>:X.Y.Z`). GoReleaser's `changelog: use: github` produces a plain
commit list; replace the release body with human notes afterward via
`gh release edit vX.Y.Z --notes-file`.
